Stage veteran actor, Lynda Gravatt dies at 76

ANI / Feb 27, 2024, 11:59 (IST)

Lynda Gravatt, a renowned actress and a founding member of Robert Alexander's Living Stage at the prestigious Arena Stage company in Washington, passed away on Friday at a hospital in New Brunswick, New Jersey. Gravatt received accolades for her performances, including a Theatre World award in 1999 for portraying Quilly McGrath in 'The Old Settler' and an AUDELCO award in 2004.
